<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1872-01-25T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1872-01-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="78" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d78">
                        <head>No. 78.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Low</persName>
                                to Mr. <persName type="to">Fish</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Extract.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                        the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1872-01-25"><hi rend="italic">January</hi> 25,
                                1872</date>. (Received April 1.)</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 129.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: * * * * * * *</p>
                        <p>The subject of providing competent interpreters for the consulates has
                            often been urged upon the attention of the Department and Congress. I
                            content myself, therefore, with the remark that the more I examine into
                            the question the more thoroughly am I convinced of the great necessity
                            of adequate provision being made by Congress to supply this deficiency,
                            both for the dignity and influence of the Government and the advancement
                            of our commercial interests in China.</p>
                        <p>I am, &amp;c,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>FREDERICK F. LOW.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>